(DATA PROCESSING AGREEMENT / AUFTRAGSVERARBEITUNGSVERTRAG) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Classification: Synthetic demo contract for Harvey hackathon use only. Not legal advice.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This Data Processing Agreement is entered into as of 15 May 2026 between BMW AG, Petuelring) Tj
T*
(130, 80788 Muenchen, Germany \(BMW or Controller\), and AtlasEdge AutoCloud GmbH,) Tj
T*
(Speicherstrasse 18, 60327 Frankfurt am Main, Germany \(Processor\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Background. BMW is evaluating AtlasEdge's connected vehicle analytics platform for warranty) Tj
T*
(triage, dealer service quality, fleet diagnostics, and over-the-air campaign readiness.) Tj
T*
(AtlasEdge will host the service and process personal data only as described in this) Tj
T*
(Agreement and the related pilot order form.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Subject Matter and Duration. Processor will provide a cloud analytics environment for) Tj
T*
(ingestion, normalization, dashboarding, and incident correlation of connected vehicle) Tj
T*
(service events. Processing begins on 1 June 2026 and continues until the earlier of pilot) Tj
T*
(termination or 31 May 2027, unless the parties sign a production order.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. BMW Instructions. Processor shall process personal data only on documented BMW) Tj
T*
(instructions. However, Processor may use pseudonymized telemetry, service ticket metadata,) Tj
T*
(and platform usage logs to improve its anomaly detection models, generate automotive) Tj
T*
(industry benchmarks, and train synthetic-data generators unless BMW objects in writing) Tj
T*
(within ten business days after signature.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. Categories of Data Subjects. Data subjects include vehicle users, drivers of BMW fleet) Tj
T*
(vehicles, dealer service advisors, BMW warranty analysts, roadside assistance coordinators,) Tj
T*
(supplier support engineers, and BMW employees participating in the pilot.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Categories of Personal Data. The service may process vehicle identification number,) Tj
T*
(pseudonymous driver profile ID, vehicle location at fault occurrence, timestamp, service) Tj
T*
(event, warranty claim identifier, dealer code, service advisor name and work email, BMW) Tj
T*
(employee user ID, diagnostic trouble codes, battery status, charging behavior, support) Tj
T*
(ticket comments, IP address, and audit log data.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. Special and Sensitive Data. The parties do not intend to process special categories of) Tj
T*
(personal data. The parties acknowledge that precise location, employee data, and driver) Tj
T*
(behavior data require heightened review, and BMW may suspend data flows until the DPIA and) Tj
T*
(any works council dependencies are complete.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. Subprocessors. Processor is generally authorized to engage subprocessors. Current) Tj
T*
(subprocessors are CloudScale EU GmbH \(Frankfurt hosting\), RouteLens Analytics S.r.l. \(Milan) Tj
T*
(route enrichment\), SupportOps India Pvt. Ltd. \(Bangalore L2 support\), and OpenMetrics Inc.) Tj
T*
(\(Virginia telemetry quality tooling\). Processor will update its online list from time to) Tj
T*
(time and provide seven days' notice before adding a new subprocessor. BMW may object only) Tj
T*
(where it proves a material unresolved security risk.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7. Third-Country Transfers. Production data will be hosted in Germany. Support personnel in) Tj
T*
(India and the United States may access service data remotely for incident response,) Tj
T*
ET
