T*
(8. Security Measures. Processor shall maintain commercially reasonable technical and) Tj
T*
(organisational measures. Annex 2 summarizes the current control set: TLS 1.2 or higher in) Tj
T*
(transit, AES-256 at rest for production databases, role-based access, MFA for) Tj
T*
(administrators, quarterly vulnerability scans, and 180-day audit log retention. Processor) Tj
T*
(may modify controls if it determines the modified controls provide materially similar) Tj
T*
(protection.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(9. Personal Data Breach. Processor will notify BMW within 72 hours after confirming that a) Tj
T*
(security incident is a personal data breach. Initial notice will describe the affected) Tj
T*
(systems if known. Processor will provide additional information after completing its) Tj
T*
(forensic investigation and after receiving approval from its incident steering committee.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(10. Data Subject Requests. Processor shall forward any data subject request to BMW within) Tj
T*
(five business days. Processor may charge professional services fees for search, export,) Tj
T*
(correction, deletion, restriction, or objection support where requests exceed two hours of) Tj
T*
(effort per calendar month.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(11. Data Subject Rights Waiver. To the fullest extent legally permissible, data subjects) Tj
T*
(waive all data subject rights against Processor for service data that BMW submits to the) Tj
T*
(platform. BMW remains responsible for notices to its employees, customers, and drivers.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(12. Audit. BMW may request a security questionnaire once per contract year. Processor will) Tj
T*
(not permit onsite audits, direct access to systems, interviews with security personnel, or) Tj
T*
(disclosure of penetration test reports. Processor may provide a management summary of) Tj
T*
(external certifications if available.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(13. Return and Deletion. After termination, Processor will make a commercially reasonable) Tj
T*
(export available for 30 days, delete active production data within 180 days, and delete) Tj
T*
(routine backups within 18 months. Processor may retain aggregated, anonymized,) Tj
T*
(pseudonymized, or synthetic data for service improvement.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(14. Confidentiality. Processor personnel with service access are subject to written) Tj
T*
(confidentiality obligations. Processor may disclose BMW data to its affiliates,) Tj
T*
(subprocessors, auditors, insurers, and professional advisors on a need-to-know basis.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(15. Liability. Processor's aggregate liability is capped at three months of fees paid under) Tj
T*
(the pilot order. The cap applies to security incidents, data protection claims, third-party) Tj
T*
(claims, and regulatory fines to the maximum extent permitted by law. Processor is not liable) Tj
T*
(for indirect, consequential, special, punitive, or loss-of-profit damages.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(16. Governing Law and Venue. This Agreement is governed by German law. The courts of Munich) Tj
T*
(have jurisdiction, except that Processor may seek payment relief in Frankfurt am Main.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Annex 1 - Processing Matrix. Purpose: warranty triage and connected service analytics.) Tj
T*
